node.text:
I have spoken a few times on my wall about what a privilege it is to have sponsors, and how reaching an agreement is so much more than just a ‘contract’. It’s about what works for the horses first, the shared values between myself the brand, and discovering more about the teams behind the company.

Below is a lovely example of this and how nice it can be when you really get to know the people behind the brands, they are horse loving people just like us! 

So today my face lit up when I received this. This is 6 years old, Eve Grace Moody,  who I first met when her mum and dad (owners of @bloomfieldshorseboxes , who I have just partnered with) came to the stables for the box handover and on learning, she is a keen rider, I let her sit on Valegro who obviously took very good care of her 🙏🏻 

Today she begged her mum to send this video to me as it was her first ever time off the lead rein, with her beautiful pony Flo. She said to her mum, Helen, that she must show her the WhatsApp to prove that she had sent the video to me😂☺️ 

Well Eve, I am very proud of you; you have done really well today and I am looking forward to seeing your riding progress.

So yes, sponsorship is of course still a huge privilege for me, and still something I am so grateful for....but even more so, when it brings about such lovely messages and moments like these x

🎧 on until the end ☺️☺️☺️☺️

node.text:
🌟🌟Driving Force - Sky Sports🌟🌟

The episode of ‘Driving Force’ featuring myself and Judy Murray is on air tomorrow night at 9pm GMT
Channel: Sky Sports Mix 
First Airing 28th December

Driving Force
Judy Murray interviews the biggest names in sport and explore stories of success, discrimination and achieving the impossible for a new Sky Sports docuseries 'Driving Force'.

The series, which started on November 24, is exclusive to Sky Sports and explores the making of athletes and the driving forces behind their success.

It aims to shine a light on inequality and other challenges in sport and has a view to calling out, educating and highlighting the need for change for future generations. Across the series, athletes lay their stories bare and unveil both the negative and positive sides of professional sport.

Hope you are able to watch and thank you to Sky for this opportunity 🙏🏻

@pow.tv_ @drivingforceseries

node.text: Our little superstar has arrived back safely this morning and straight to his happy place 🎃 ❤️❤️

node.text: Some of you may have seen on Good Morning Britain that my mum has been very ill of late and is currently in hospital. She found all her strength to watch and support me whilst I was in Tokyo, so it is lovely to see her today, take some silly photos, have a giggle and show her my medals. I love you mum. X
